"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450447","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-08","<p>We no longer have customer access phones in Jobcentres. However, should a claimant need to use a telephone in connection with their claim or job search, they will be given access to a phone by their work coach.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-02-08T16:14:32.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450447/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450447/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-03","Universal Credit: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether telephones with a direct connection to the universal credit helpline are available to use free of charge in every job centre.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","25760"
