"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450525","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-10","<p>The information on benefit receipt by nationality is not available.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has published statistics on working age benefit recipients claiming within 6 months of National Insurance Number (NINO) registration. This information is known as “Nationality at point of National Insurance number registration of DWP benefit claimants” and is included in the “Statistical Bulletin on National Insurance Number Allocations to Adult Overseas Nationals”.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is looking at ways to reform the current administrative system under Universal Credit so that it will systematically record nationality and immigration status of migrants who make a claim.</p>",,"Lord Freud","HL5888 ; HL5890","2016-02-10T15:14:48.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450525/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450525/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/450525/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-03","Social Security Benefits: EU Nationals","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what proportion of EU immigrants were in receipt of benefit payments during the last two years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Lord Turnberg",,"Lord Turnberg","HL5887"
