"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449747","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-09","<p>The Department of Business, Innovation and Skills HQ, as at 31 January 2016, employed (a) no people in Salford and Eccles constituency and (b) 38 people in Greater Manchester.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-02-09T17:29:26.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449747/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449747/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449747/answer",,,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-02","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many people are employed by his Department in (a) Salford and Eccles constituency and (b) Greater Manchester.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","25363"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449748","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-04","<p>Details of Ministers' meetings with external organisations, including senior media figures, are published routinely and can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications</a> on Gov.uk.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-02-04T09:30:39.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449748/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449748/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449748/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-02","Cabinet Office: Sky","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what meetings (a) Ministers and (b) civil servants in his Department have had with (i) James Murdoch and (ii) representatives from Sky UK Limited in each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Maria Eagle","Garston and Halewood","Maria Eagle","25378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449749","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-05","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p><p>Departments publish, on their pages on GOV.UK, quarterly reports on the percentage of undisputed invoices they pay within 5 and 30 days. From the start of the next financial year they will also report quarterly on their liability to pay interest under the Late Payment of Commercial Debts (Interest) Act 1998.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-02-05T14:28:15.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449749/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449749/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449749/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-02","Government Departments: Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, on how many occasions government departments have paid bills to private businesses more than 60 days after the date the invoice was received since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","25347"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449750","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-10","<p>Information on the stock of UK assets, or money owed by other countries to the UK, is captured in the UK’s International Investment Position. A country by country breakdown is available in table 10.2 of the 2015 ONS Pink Book which can be found here: <a href="http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/publications/re-reference-tables.html?edition=tcm%3A77-382775" target="_blank">http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/publications/re-reference-tables.html?edition=tcm%3A77-382775</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-02-10T16:33:33.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449750/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449750/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449750/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-02","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much was owed to the UK by which countries in the last year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Sir David Crausby","Bolton North East","Mr David Crausby","25443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449751","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-05","<p>Details of Ministers' meetings with external organisations, including senior media figures, are published routinely and can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications</a> on Gov.uk.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-02-05T09:09:09.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449751/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449751/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449751/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-02","Cabinet Office: Uber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many meetings Ministers and officials of his Department have had with representatives of Uber in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","25294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449752","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-05","<p>Guidance to UK civil servants on conducting consultations during the period prior to elections for devolved national assemblies will be issued in due course as part of broader guidance issued on conduct during this time.</p><p> </p>","West Dorset","Mr Oliver Letwin",,"2016-02-05T09:10:23.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449752/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Letwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449752/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449752/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-02","Public Consultation: Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether elections for devolved national assemblies are included within the reference to local and national elections in paragraph K of his Department's Consultation Principles 2016, published on 14 January 2016.","false","Biography information for Ms Harriet Harman","Camberwell and Peckham","Ms Harriet Harman","25296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449753","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-05","<p>The Government Property Unit is working closely with Oldham Council and others across Greater Manchester on future plans across the public sector estate. Oldham Council is part of the Greater Manchester Combined Authority Partnership in the One Public Estate Programme delivered by Cabinet Office and the Local Government Association. The GMCA’s plans on what land and property will be disposed are still being developed and have not yet been identified. The partnership was awarded £250,000 in December 2015 on joining Phase 3 of the programme. Overall it expects to generate £172 million capital receipts, and create 30,000 new homes and 43,000 new jobs over the next 5 years. GMCA's programme also includes the establishment of a Land Commission, which will help to deliver 10,000 new homes per year.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-02-05T14:28:02.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449753/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449753/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449753/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-02","Public Sector: Oldham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what land and property in Oldham his Department has identified for disposal over the next five years as part of the One Public Estate programme; and if he will estimate (a) the number of jobs that will be created, (b) housing that will be built and (c) capital receipts that will be accrued as a result of the sale of those sites.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","25342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449754","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-10","<p>In Q3 2015 household debt fell to 142 per cent of household income, down from its peak of 168 per cent in Q1 2008. The Government’s plan for a higher wage, lower welfare society makes it easier for families and working people to save, and includes the new National Living Wage which will mean a pay boost for 1.7 million workers this year.</p><p> </p><p>Nonetheless, the Government recognises that there are those who face problem levels of debt. The Money Advice Service (MAS) is responsible for the coordination of publically funded free to client debt advice and is financed by a levy on the financial services industry. MAS is currently consulting on its business plan; it has proposed levying for a constant debt advice budget for 2016/17 providing around £45 million.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is currently reviewing how the public provision of free-to-client, impartial financial guidance, including consumer debt advice services, should be structured. The Public Financial Guidance consultation closed in December 2015 and the Government will report back by budget.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally, we have created the independent Financial Policy Committee within the Bank of England, to ensure emerging risks and vulnerabilities across the financial system as a whole, including in relation to household debt, are identified, monitored and effectively addressed.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","25270","2016-02-10T12:34:49.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449754/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449754/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449754/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-02","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department is taking to reduce levels of personal debt and household borrowing.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","25302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449755","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-05","I refer the hon Member to the answer that I gave to the hon Member for Birmingham, Ladywood (Shabana Mahmood) on 26 February 2015. Link below:<p> </p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2014-12-15/218658/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2014-12-15/218658/</a></p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-02-05T14:56:55.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449755/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449755/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449755/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-02","Revenue and Customs: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many transfer pricing experts have been employed by HM Revenue and Customs in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","25343"
