"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449757","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-08","<p>The government does not plan to revise the eligibility criteria for the Help to Buy: ISA scheme.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-02-08T16:40:47.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449757/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449757/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449757/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-02","Help to Buy Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the Government plans to increase the £250,000 threshold for properties outside London under the Help to Buy ISA scheme.","false","Biography information for Mr Mark Prisk","Hertford and Stortford","Mr Mark Prisk","25319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449758","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-05","<p>Treasury Ministers and officials have meetings with a wide variety of organisations in the public and private sectors as part of the process of policy development and delivery.</p><p> </p><p>Details of ministerial and permanent secretary meetings with external organisations on departmental business are published on a quarterly basis and are available via the gov.uk website</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-02-05T13:51:04.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449758/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449758/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449758/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-02","Uber","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many meetings Ministers and officials of his Department have had with representatives of Uber in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","25295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449759","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-10","<p>All self-employed taxi drivers are subject to the same rules when calculating trading profits chargeable to tax.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-02-10T16:40:58.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449759/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449759/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449759/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-02","Taxis: Income Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will estimate the proportion of tax to income paid by (a) an Uber taxi driver, (b) a black cab driver and (c) a mini cab driver.","false","Biography information for Tom Elliott","Fermanagh and South Tyrone","Tom Elliott","25311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449760","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-05","<p>To provide the answer to these questions would incur disproportionate cost. Data has not been captured centrally for the specific categories over the last 10 years.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","25290","2016-02-05T14:58:12.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449760/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449760/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449760/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-02","Internet: Fraud","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many prosecutions for VAT and customs fraud relating to online sales and imports there have been in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Rob Marris","Wolverhampton South West","Rob Marris","25289"
